{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"438ebae6-1171-41cc-8cda-db0e53261f05","content":"**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ This is correct for .NET MAUI. You need the platform-specific namespace:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\nThis automatically insets page content to avoid the notch/home indicator.\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid** — ❌ This property **does not exist** in .NET MAUI. The tutorial is likely outdated or mixing in Xamarin.Forms concepts.\n\n### Background image behind the safe area\n\nInstead, **don't** set `UseSafeArea` on the page and manually pad your content:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"...\">\n    <!-- No UseSafeArea — background fills entire screen -->\n    <Grid>\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n        \n        <!-- Content grid with safe-area padding -->\n        <Grid Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='20,44,20,34'}\">\n            <!-- your UI here -->\n        </Grid>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nOr programmatically read the safe area insets via `On<iOS>().SafeAreaInsets()` for dynamic values, which is more robust across different iPhone models.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"00a71133-070f-411f-9e9b-52722c5cbfbe","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - a property on Grid\n\nLet me check what I know about these APIs in .NET MAUI, particularly for .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the iOS safe area handling is done via platform-specifics. The correct API is:\n\n- `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - This is the iOS platform-specific for handling safe areas on pages. The namespace is `xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"`.\n\n\n- `IgnoreSafeArea` doesn't actually exist in .NET MAUI as a property on Grid or other layouts. That was a Xamarin.Forms concept, and the approach changed in .NET MAUI where safe area handling is managed through the platform-specific `UseSafeArea` property on pages instead.\n\n- For extending a background image behind the safe area while keeping content within bounds, I'd need to either disable `UseSafeArea` and manually manage padding, or use a different layout strategy altogether.\n\nLet me be honest about the limitations here—.NET 10 is still upcoming, so I should stick with what I know works in current MAUI versions rather than speculating about future changes.","outputTokens":1149,"requestId":"943F:763D5:1517BC2:1775F31:6A066F7E"},"id":"80164e05-af99-4cf2-8607-3eb63a17fb69","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:57:59.760Z","parentId":"db730927-721c-458e-8a48-5f4bd2f8f4ac"}
